50
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,559
You need to tackle those hurdles

51
00:03:15,559 --> 00:03:16,439
bit by bit.

52
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,400
I'll skip this one.

53
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,279
But I'll go next time, okay?

54
00:03:18,439 --> 00:03:19,599
Are you kidding me?

55
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:20,879
This is for your own good.

56
00:03:20,879 --> 00:03:21,439
And besides,

57
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:23,039
you don't take piano lessons now.

58
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,360
Why bother with the performance?

59
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,520
What's the point?

60
00:03:25,599 --> 00:03:26,839
I'm doing this for you!

61
00:03:26,839 --> 00:03:28,080
No, that's not true.

62
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,319
You're doing it for yourself!

63
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,680
Ever since mom got pregnant,

64
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:31,319
you haven't cared about

65
00:03:31,319 --> 00:03:32,200
anything at home.

66
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:33,080
When the new baby comes,

67
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,360
you'll probably forget all about me.

68
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:35,559
I don't care?

69
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,400
I've been helping with

70
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:36,960
your homework...

71
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:37,680
Enough, enough.

72
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:38,599
Just stop arguing!

73
00:03:38,599 --> 00:03:39,559
You think I don't care?

74
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:47,520
Look,

75
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:48,319
Yunjie,

76
00:03:48,559 --> 00:03:49,559
there's still time before

77
00:03:49,599 --> 00:03:50,640
the entrance exam.

78
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:53,159
I've got an idea.

79
00:03:53,279 --> 00:03:54,759
How about I pull some strings

80
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,120
and get Yunjie into

81
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,960
the top school in our county?

82
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:58,559
What do you think?

83
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:02,480
Good.

84
00:04:02,839 --> 00:04:03,400
Great idea!

85
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,279
It's decided then.

86
00:04:04,839 --> 00:04:05,400
Dad!

87
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,800
What?

88
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,319
Your dad

89
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:11,559
went to that school years ago.

90
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:12,640
Ask him.

91
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:14,400
It's a strict school,

92
00:04:14,599 --> 00:04:16,480
and you have to study hard there.

93
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,039
Even your cousin Huahua

94
00:04:18,039 --> 00:04:20,599
got into a university in Beijing

95
00:04:20,599 --> 00:04:21,719
from there.

96
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:22,839
Got it?

97
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:23,800
I'm not going!

98
00:04:24,879 --> 00:04:25,399
Hey,

99
00:04:25,639 --> 00:04:26,920
do you have something cooking on the stove?

100
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,360
I smell something burning.

101
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:30,480
Oh no, I forgot!

102
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,199
Please, be good, okay?

103
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,319
Auntie got too busy and forgot.

104
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:35,680
I don't care.

105
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:36,840
I'm not going.

106
00:04:36,959 --> 00:04:37,920
I want to be in the performance!

107
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,160
So?

108
00:04:52,559 --> 00:04:53,720
I said what I needed to.

109
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,160
Well, you blew it.

110
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:57,120
Fine, let's see if you can do better.

111
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:01,319
I won't give up easily.

112
00:05:10,439 --> 00:05:11,519
Let's see what you've got.

113
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:14,959
I told you before,

114
00:05:15,079 --> 00:05:16,439
you can't raise a kid like that.

115
00:05:16,439 --> 00:05:16,999
But you...

116
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:19,079
It's important to find the right approach.

117
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,800
But you insist on doing it your way.

118
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,759
You just don't get it.

119
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:23,639
Just leave it to me.

120
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:26,040
And I've done

121
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,079
a great job so far.

122
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,040
You just have to...

123
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,160
Now she's upset.

124
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:29,879
She might even

125
00:05:29,879 --> 00:05:31,040
smash the piano.

126
00:06:10,519 --> 00:06:11,319
That's beautiful.

127
00:06:13,639 --> 00:06:14,519
You know,

128
00:06:14,959 --> 00:06:17,199
every day when I leave for work,

129
00:06:17,199 --> 00:06:18,360
the moment I step out that door,

130
00:06:18,439 --> 00:06:19,199
I feel like

131
00:06:19,199 --> 00:06:20,639
I'm going into battle.

132
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,559
But when I step through this door,

133
00:06:22,879 --> 00:06:23,680
I think to myself,

134
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,480
this home is just perfect.

135
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:26,120
I've got such a

136
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,399
wonderful daughter.

137
00:06:28,399 --> 00:06:29,199
And my heart

138
00:06:29,759 --> 00:06:32,240
softens right up.

139
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,999
I feel my heart

140
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,199
is wrapped in love

141
00:06:38,199 --> 00:06:39,439
and contentment.

142
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,600
That's vivid.

143
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,439
I should jot this down.

144
00:06:43,439 --> 00:06:45,040
I might use it for my next essay.

145
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,240
Don't change the subject, okay?

146
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,199
I'm, after all,

147
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,079
a journalism graduate.

148
00:06:49,079 --> 00:06:49,439
OK?

149
00:06:49,439 --> 00:06:50,840
I know how to be sentimental.

150
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:52,040
You're good at liberal arts.

151
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,040
You get that from me.

152
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,319
Dad always says,

153
00:06:54,319 --> 00:06:55,079
I'm not good at science,

154
00:06:55,079 --> 00:06:56,280
and that's your fault too.

155
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:59,120
I'd say his genes

156
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,879
just couldn't beat mine.

157
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:04,639
Mom, you

158
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:06,399
never lose an argument.

159
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,120
Not always.

160
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,280
Sometimes

161
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,800
when I can't find the right words,

162
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,040
I'll lose.

163
00:07:12,639 --> 00:07:14,439
When I think about it later,

164
00:07:15,399 --> 00:07:15,999
I regret not saying

165
00:07:15,999 --> 00:07:17,199
those few lines.

166
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:17,840
Right?

167
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:18,439
Exactly!

168
00:07:18,559 --> 00:07:19,519
That's the feeling!

169
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:20,360
Spot on.

170
00:07:22,439 --> 00:07:23,439
It's all a strategy.

171
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,079
Mom,

172
00:07:26,840 --> 00:07:28,959
what did the teacher talk to you about?

173
00:07:30,959 --> 00:07:31,879
Oh, nothing much.

174
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,199
She just showed me

175
00:07:33,199 --> 00:07:34,800
some of your test papers.

176
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,840
Your teacher also said,

177
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:37,920
you've had a lot of new material

178
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,720
to learn lately.

179
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:40,519
So you haven't had

180
00:07:40,519 --> 00:07:42,240
much time to review.

181
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:43,519
Let's take some time

182
00:07:43,519 --> 00:07:44,800
to go over the new stuff, okay?

183
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:46,040
Just consolidate what you've learned,

184
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,720
and your grades will go up.

185
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:48,600
Right?

186
00:07:49,519 --> 00:07:50,720
But I've been

187
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,240
so exhausted lately.

188
00:07:53,879 --> 00:07:55,079
That's common.

189
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:57,040
I'm stressed too.

190
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,319
You know I'm pregnant

191
00:07:58,319 --> 00:07:59,079
and still working.

192
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:00,800
I have to be extra careful at the office.

193
00:08:00,879 --> 00:08:02,120
I can't afford any mistakes.

194
00:08:02,319 --> 00:08:03,639
Plus, I'm training new hires.

195
00:08:03,639 --> 00:08:05,160
I've also got to assign all the work

196
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,559
before taking my maternity leave.

197
00:08:06,759 --> 00:08:07,600
If I don't

198
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,680
plan everything well,

199
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,680
when I come back from leave,

200
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,680
I might not have a job waiting for me.

201
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:11,800
Is it really that serious?

202
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:12,920
What do you think?

203
00:08:13,399 --> 00:08:14,160
Let me tell you,

204
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,600
the workplace is brutal.

205
00:08:15,879 --> 00:08:17,600
Doing a good job doesn't always
guarantee promotions or raises.

206
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,160
But if you screw up,

207
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,639
and you're definitely getting the boot.

208
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,160
Playing the pity card?

209
00:08:23,639 --> 00:08:25,439
Getting into high school isn't easy either.

210
00:08:25,879 --> 00:08:26,680
So,

211
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,319
let's work hard together,

212
00:08:28,399 --> 00:08:28,999
shall we?

213
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:30,959
We can set a schedule

214
00:08:31,079 --> 00:08:32,639
and stick to it.

215
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:34,079
You focus on studying for exams,

216
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,399
and I'll focus on having this baby.

217
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,959
It's just six months,

218
00:08:37,399 --> 00:08:38,959
we'll get through it.

219
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:43,519
Mom,

220
00:08:44,799 --> 00:08:45,639
I feel like

221
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:46,399
Dad,

222
00:08:46,399 --> 00:08:48,200
he doesn't like me as much anymore.

223
00:08:49,799 --> 00:08:50,759
How could that be?

224
00:08:50,759 --> 00:08:51,759
My sweet girl,

225
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:53,080
that's impossible.

226
00:08:55,639 --> 00:08:56,560
Honestly,

227
00:08:56,919 --> 00:08:58,720
I haven't fully come to terms

228
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:01,200
with you having another baby.

229
00:09:01,639 --> 00:09:03,279
But recently,

230
00:09:03,399 --> 00:09:04,440
Grandpa has been sick,

231
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,759
Auntie had an early delivery,

232
00:09:05,759 --> 00:09:06,960
and you need bed rest,

233
00:09:07,879 --> 00:09:10,039
I think I need to be more grown-up about it.

234
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:12,600
You've been through so much.

235
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:13,399
My poor baby.

236
00:09:14,279 --> 00:09:14,720
Honey.

237
00:09:14,919 --> 00:09:15,320
I'm here.

238
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,960
Hurry up. Say something.

239
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:17,960
Your daughter even thinks

240
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,080
you don't love her anymore.

241
00:09:19,999 --> 00:09:21,240
What? That's not true!

242
00:09:25,159 --> 00:09:26,999
How could I not love you?

243
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:30,120
You're my daughter, Yunjie.

244
00:09:30,399 --> 00:09:32,080
I still remember it like yesterday

245
00:09:32,639 --> 00:09:34,159
the first time I held you in my arms.

246
00:09:34,999 --> 00:09:36,399
When you were just born,

247
00:09:37,279 --> 00:09:38,600
the nurse handed you to me

248
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:40,840
and told me to hold you a bit higher.

249
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,039
Your tiny head

250
00:09:43,039 --> 00:09:44,399
was snuggled right up against me.

251
00:09:45,399 --> 00:09:46,560
I was so tense that

252
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:47,960
my upper body was frozen.

253
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,279
I couldn't even move.

254
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,639
I was terrified that if I did,

255
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,440
I might hurt you.

256
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,200
But I was so happy.

257
00:09:59,799 --> 00:10:00,600
It was the first time

258
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:03,039
I'd ever felt such pure joy.

259
00:10:08,159 --> 00:10:09,519
And then the first time

260
00:10:09,919 --> 00:10:11,039
I took you to kindergarten.

261
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,720
The first day of elementary school.

262
00:10:14,999 --> 00:10:16,560
The first day of middle school.

263
00:10:22,039 --> 00:10:23,399
All those firsts,

264
00:10:24,039 --> 00:10:25,560
no one else could give me that.

265
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,600
Yunjie,

266
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:51,519
this whole second child thing

267
00:10:51,919 --> 00:10:54,279
it's not as heavy as you think.

268
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,399
Do you know what your teacher

269
00:10:55,399 --> 00:10:56,679
said about this?

270
00:10:57,159 --> 00:10:57,720
She said,

271
00:10:58,840 --> 00:10:59,600
it's like playing a game.

272
00:10:59,759 --> 00:11:00,679
You're like the main account.

273
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,759
The second child is like an alt account.

274
00:11:01,999 --> 00:11:03,639
Even if we're leveling up the alt,

275
00:11:03,639 --> 00:11:04,560
we still

276
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:07,679
keep the main account logged in.

277
00:11:07,999 --> 00:11:09,560
What kind of comparison that?

278
00:11:10,399 --> 00:11:11,999
Well, it might sound odd, but it's true.

279
00:11:12,679 --> 00:11:13,279
Yeah.

280
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:18,320
You're a teenager now.

281
00:11:18,759 --> 00:11:19,759
We know

282
00:11:19,919 --> 00:11:21,639
you have the urge to push boundaries

283
00:11:21,879 --> 00:11:23,120
and to break free.

284
00:11:23,879 --> 00:11:26,080
But we don't

285
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,759
want you to

286
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,039
push us away.

287
00:11:31,159 --> 00:11:32,840
I'm not trying to oppose you.

288
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:35,080
And it's not that I don't
want to attend the lecture.

289
00:11:36,159 --> 00:11:36,759
I just want to

290
00:11:36,759 --> 00:11:38,240
end my piano journey

291
00:11:38,279 --> 00:11:40,080
on a high note.

292
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,039
Didn't you always say

293
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,240
to finish what you start?

294
00:11:44,639 --> 00:11:45,679
